Kosovo District (Serbian: Косовски округ/Kosovski okrug pronounced [kôsoʋskiː ôkruːɡ], Albanian: Distrikti i Kosoves) was a district of Kosovo and Metohija between 1990 and 1999; at that time, Kosovo was part of Serbia. The district still exists de jure, despite the fact that Serbian government accepted civil UN administration over Kosovo.
It was located in the middle and had a population of 672,292. Its capital was Pristina.